Radius is a fast-growing, startup in the heart of San Francisco. Radius applies advanced data science to deliver the freshest, accurate, and comprehensive view of 20M+ US companies―from small businesses to the largest enterprises -- to our robust portfolio of customers. We build cutting-edge machine learning solutions that help our customers discover markets, acquire customers, and measure performance through an app that’s intuitive, secure, and enterprise-ready.As a Data Scientist on the Insights team, you will be responsible for helping build and continuously improve the quality of our Network of Record, by solving complex and ambiguous problems and working cross-functionally throughout the pipeline to drive quality improvements. In this role, you will own identifying and generating the metrics needed to monitor the quality of The Network of Record. In addition, you will be conducting research into understanding the dynamics of Radius data and how it can be better utilized to deliver value to our customers.Responsibilities:Analyze and become intimately familiar with our data sources and our data processing pipeline with the goal of improving The Network of RecordProvide teams with ad-hoc analysis, reports and dashboards reflecting the state and quality of the data, leveraging best statistical practicesDevelop new methodologies for data validationWork with business stakeholders and customers to define operational solutions to data problems, and guide these solutions through to productionDrive data-driven decision making throughout the companyRequirements:2+ years experience using Python for analyzing or processing dataFluency extracting insights from sizable data setsCurious and passionate about understanding dataExperience with statistical analysis languages such as R and SQLDegree in statistics or related field or related experienceExperience using ML models to solve business problemsAdditional Preferred Qualifications:Experience coding in an object-oriented language: Java, C++, Scala, etc.Experience with distributed computing frameworks such as Spark and HadoopProfessional experience running ETL or similar processes on large datasetsComfortable working in Linux environmentRadius is an Equal Opportunity Employer.Apply NowSave
